Both output files are written and validated.

**Headline finding:** the only meaningful treatment-effect heterogeneity in the cohort is **sotorasib × KRAS-G12C × sex_female**. In KRAS-G12C-mutant MALES (n=3,508, 7% of cohort), sotorasib raises mean PFS from 3.23 → 7.88 months (+4.64 mo, p<1e-300), homogeneous across histology and slightly amplified by older age. KRAS+ females show essentially no benefit (-0.01 mo). The other three "canonical" pairings (osimertinib×EGFR, olaparib×BRCA2, pembrolizumab×TMB/PDL1) are flat across all subgroup definitions tested — single-stratum, pairwise interactions, 3-way modifiers, and random-forest CATE. Notably, STK11 does NOT suppress the sotorasib effect in this dataset; sex does.

Files written:
- `transcript.json` (20 iterations, 50 hypotheses, 50 analyses, validates against `transcript_schema.json`)
- `analysis_summary.txt` (full narrative)
